data.text:
Description

The Wells Fargo Bank is located in St Augustine, Florida. The building was constructed in 1928 and known as the First National Bank of St. Augustine. It reopened after 1929 as the Exchange Bank for several years. It later became Atlantic Bank, and then, First Union. First Union National Bank later merged with Wachovia Bank, then was bought out by Wells Fargo. This is a contributing building on the National Register of Historic Places (NRIS #70000847).
